Installation of Github with IDE'S

1. Download and install the NodeJS.

Website : https://nodejs.org/en/download/
file name : node-v6.11.0-x64.msi


2. Download webstrom IDE
	website : https://www.jetbrains.com/webstorm/download/#section=windows

	file name : WebStrom-2017.1.4.exe


3. Create the Account with GitHub.
	website : https://github.com/join
	[Note. we need to Authenticate the email receives from github]

4. Checkout the code from the cloud repository.
	URL : https://github.com/ajsnaresh/AJS_Classes.git

5. install the bower automation plugin
	>npm install -g bower.


6. download and install the mongodb.
	website  : https://www.mongodb.com/download-center#community
	filename : mongodb-win32-x86_64-2008plus-ssl-3.4.6-signed.msi

7. Download and install the REST Client (Postman)

	website : https://app.getpostman.com/app/download/win64
	file name : Postman-win64-5.0.2-Setup.exe

8. Install the gulp
	> npm install -g gulp



Push the Code to the Cloud Repository from WebStrom IDE.

1. ctrl + k

        ---> enter the commit message

            --> Commit & Push.


Pull the Code from the Cloud Repository with Webstrom IDE.

    VCS  -->  Git ---> Pull ---> select AngularJS_6PM ---> Pull.





Mongodb Installation Steps.
---------------------------
C:/data/db

Set the classpath variables for MongoDB Execution.
--------------------------------------------------
path = C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.4\bin


